1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,200
Science has a clearer story about healthy user bias than social media does.

2
00:00:05,200 --> 00:00:11,600
Healthy user bias suggests that people who engage in health behaviors often report better health outcomes.

3
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,800
But hold on!

4
00:00:12,800 --> 00:00:14,400
Not all studies agree.

5
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:20,000
Some research shows that this bias could inflate the perceived benefits of healthy habits.

6
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:26,000
In fact, individuals who are already healthy are more likely to seek out health information.

7
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:31,600
So, while healthy user bias exists, the story is complex and requires careful interpretation.

8
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:33,600
Curious about more science insights?

